Lean agile principle:  SAFe approach deals with fundamental philosophies. So  that we can assure that those principles are well applicable in  our case. If those said practices are not applicable directly, the  primary principles may guide you to ensure they are moving on  a continuous lane towards the “shortest sustainable lead time,  along with the high quality and value to people and society.”

- ## Principles
#Principles #SAFe #Frameworks #Scaling #Agile #Practices #Software #Product #Management 
Real agile teams and trains  We can say, real agile teams and trains are fully cross- functional. Those are having everything and everyone who are  needed for the fully equipped, workable and tested solution.  They organize and manage their selves, so they benefit in value  to tide more rapidly with a lesser overhead. ‘Product  Management’, ‘System Architecture’, ‘System Engineering’  and ‘Release Train Engineer’ provide content and technical  authority, and an effective process of development. ‘Product  Owners’ and ‘Scrum Masters’ use to help Development teams  to complete their work-items.

Cadence and Synchronization  Cadence delivers a recurring pattern; we can say it’s a  trustworthy heart-beat of the development process. Similarly,  synchronization allows various angles to understand and  resolve at the same time.

- ## Principles
#Principles #SAFe #Frameworks #Scaling #Agile #Practices #Software #Product #Management 
PI Planning  The most powerful event in the SAFe is PI planning. It’s  the foundation of the ‘Program Increment (PI)’, which provides  the rhythm for the ART. When many people work together to  achieve a common goal, vision, and purpose; it’s incredible  how much alignment and energy it creates.

- ## Principles
#Principles #SAFe #Frameworks #Scaling #Agile #Practices #Software #Product #Management 
System Demo  This is a primary measure of the ART’s progress. It is the  objective evidence provided by a working solution. It is in the  system demo in every two weeks. The demo includes  demonstration of full system (including integrated work of all  teams on the train) for that iteration. Generally, it is demoed to  the train’s stakeholders; after that, they may provide the  feedback, so that the train needs to stay on course and take  corrective action.

- ## Principles
#Principles #SAFe #Frameworks #Scaling #Agile #Practices #Software #Product #Management 
Inspect and Adapt  ‘Inspect and Adapt’ is a noteworthy event held every PI. To  reflect, collect data and solve problems, it’s a continuous cycle.  ‘Inspect and adapt’ assembles two components - teams and  stakeholders for assessing the solution. It also defines and takes  action on perfections required to rise in the velocity, quality,  and reliability of the next PI.

- ## Principles
#Principles #SAFe #Frameworks #Scaling #Agile #Practices #Software #Product #Management 
IP Iteration  IP means ‘Innovation and Planning’. IP iteration arises  every PI and attends several purposes. It acts as an appraising  buffer for meeting PI purposes and delivers dedicated time for  innovation, enduring education, and PI planning. It is like  additional oxygen in the tank; without this, the train may start  damaging under the autocracy of the criticality.

- ## Principles
#Principles #SAFe #Frameworks #Scaling #Agile #Practices #Software #Product #Management 
Architectural Runway  ‘Architectural runway’ contains the existing code,  components and technical infrastructure, which is necessary to  sustain operation of high priority and redesign. Without  sufficient investment in the architectural runway, the train will  slow down, needing to redesign for each new feature.

- ## Principles
#Principles #SAFe #Frameworks #Scaling #Agile #Practices #Software #Product #Management 
Lean Agile Leadership  For SAFe to be operative, the enterprise’s leaders and  managers are must supposed to take responsibility for Lean- Agile adoption and its success. Executives must become  leaders. Without leadership for the execution, the revolution  will likely fail to accomplish the full of its benefits.

Let us understand this concept in details with example. Let  us consider a real-time scenario where there are two  Proceedings of the International Conference on Inventive Computing and Informatics (ICICI 2017) IEEE Xplore Compliant - Part Number: CFP17L34-ART, ISBN: 978-1-5386-4031-9 978-1-5386-4031-9/17/$31.00 ©2017 IEEE 794independent teams working under different agile models. Let’s  say them as ‘team A’ and ‘team B’. Team A is facing some  issue while working on a critical work-item. In addition, it  needs an API/View (i.e. source of data to refer) to consume to  complete that particular work-item. ‘Team B’ owns the data in  API/View. So ‘team B’ should expose that API/View.  However, that ad-hoc work-item does not fit in the iteration  cycle of ‘team B’. Therefore, it adds unnecessary delay in the  work-item of ‘team A’ due to bandwidth dependency

- ## Challenges
#Challenges #Scaling #Agile #Practices #Software #Product #Management 
Generally, every team has its own framework of implanting  agile methodology. Some teams deals with ‘scrum’ based agile  model, somewhere its ‘Kanban’, some of them use ‘scrum-ban’  version of agile. This way every team has its own set of  processes and preconditions. Their iteration duration and cycle  also differs with their convenience. So it becomes very clumsy  to make two teams operate in-line with dependency. [1, 2].
